nhyAbout This BBS
nhr-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nwNaClCON BBS is the semi-official community hub for NaClCON 2026 -- the hacker
nwconference on the coast of Carolina Beach, NC. Running Synchronet v3.21 on AWS.
nwConnect before, during, and after the con. Message boards, file areas, chat,
nwexternal doors, and The Pelican.

nhyHow to Connect
nhr-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nw  SSH on port 2222:
nc    ssh -p 2222 <yourname>@100.51.222.185
nw  New users can register on connect. No invite needed.

nhyWhat's Here
nhr-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nw  [x] SSH access on port 2222
nw  [x] New user registration
nw  [x] NaClCON branding throughout
nw  [x] Local message boards
nw  [x] Chat, file areas, external doors
nw  [x] Security hardening (rate limiting, IP bans, login throttling)
nw  [x] Shell restricted to Synchronet Classic + Deuce's Lightbar Shell
nw  [x] Speaker list and per-speaker message threads
nw  [x] ANSI art splash screens (terminal-adaptive)
nw  [x] The Pelican -- Claude-powered AI chat bot (1-on-1 and multinode)

nhyWhat's Coming
nhr-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nw  [ ] CTF-related content
nw  [ ] Custom doors / programs
nw  [ ] Browser terminal -- connect from a web browser, no SSH client needed

nhyThe Pelican
nhr-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
nwThe Pelican is the BBS chat bot -- a sassy southern coastal Peli-hen who
nwknows her way around a terminal. She has opinions about hacker culture,
nwthe beach, and good seafood. Powered by the Claude API (Haiku model).
nwShe knows NaClCON inside and out, has read every issue of Phrack, the
nwHacker's Manifesto, the DoD Rainbow Series, and Neuromancer.
nwChat 1-on-1 from the Chat menu, or find her in multinode chat.

